Mini project Title : To-Do List with priority
Information :A working to-do list that allows:</br>
             <ul><li>Adding tasks with priority</li></br>
             <li>Optional due dates</li></br>
             <li>Deleting tasks</li><br>
             <li>Tasks are sorted by priority and date</li></ul></br>
  
Prepare a concise presentation covering the following points: </br>
</br>
1)	Problem Statement: Describe the problem your project addresses. </br>
</br>
<ul><li>A simple task management app where users can add, edit, delete, and mark tasks as completed.</ul></li></br>
</br>
2)	Objective: Explain the purpose of your project. </br>

<ul><li>Allow users to create and manage tasks</li>
<li>Categorize tasks by priority: High, Medium, Low</li>
<li>Improve time management using due dates</li>
<li>Simple, clean user interface using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript</li></ul>

3)	Goal: Define the end goals and intended outcomes of your project. </br>

<ul><li>Add task with title, priority, and due date</li>
<li>Tasks sorted by priority</li>
<li>Delete tasks</li>
<li>Simple and responsive design</li>
<li>Works offline (no Firebase, no login)</li></ul>


4)	Technology Used: List the tools, languages, or frameworks you used. </br>
<ul><li>HTML  Structure of the webpage</li>
<li>CSS  Styling and layout</li>
<li>JavaScript  Logic and interactivity</li>
<li>Visual Studio Code  Code editor</li>
<li>Live Server Local testing</li></ul>

5)	User Audience: Identify the target audience or users of your project. </br>
<ul><li>This simple To-Do list is for people who use Offline and online To-do list tasks.This is a simple and accurate to prioratize ,add and delete the To-do List.</li></ul></br>

6)	Impact on Society: Discuss how your project could benefit society or people in general.</br>
<ul><li>This simple TO-Do list helps anyone without age limit to create simple daily TO-Do list.</ul></li></br>
